<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Lycium</i> <i>californicum</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>nesiotica</i>, <i>Arthrocnemum</i> <i>subterminale</i>, <i>Bergerocactus</i> <i>emoryi</i>, <i>Coreopsis</i> <i>gigantea</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>prolifera</i>, <i>Encelia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>giganteum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>grande</i> var. <i>timorum</i>, <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>oricola</i> and <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i>. Herbs occur at varying cover including <i>Amblyopappus</i> <i>pusillus</i>, <i>Amsinckia</i> <i>menziesii</i> var. <i>intermedia</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>diandrus</i>, <i>Dichelostemma</i> <i>capitatum</i>, <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Erodium</i> spp., <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i> or <i>Mesembryanthemum</i> <i>crystallinum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 4 m; canopy is open to intermittent. Herbaceous layer is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Lycium californicum</i> > 30% relative cover or characteristically present in the shrub canopy with a mixture of other shrubs including <i>Rhus integrifolia, Encelia californica, Cylindropuntia prolifera,</i> and <i>Suaeda taxifolia </i>(Buck-Diaz and Evens 2015, Sproul et al. 2011, Verdone and Evens 2010).</li>
		
		<li><i>Lycium californicum </i>> 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal bluffs and terraces. Soils are sandy or gravelly.  </div>
</div>

        
