<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">While <i>Lycium californicum </i> is able to tolerate fire by resprouting, fire is likely infrequent in stands of this maritime succulent alliance. A study on San Clemente Island used prescribed burning to evaluate fire effects in this alliance, yet was limited to degraded stands, with the following results: <i>Lycium californicum</i> cover markedly decreased after fire but exhibited resprouting, <i>Lycium</i> did not show postfire seedling recruitment, no obviously fire-dependent species occurred in this community, and fire favored non-native species at the expense of native species, although the effect was not substantial (Keeley and Brennan 2015).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
